runs.comm: edged and just wide of first slip diving high to his right, nearly the perfect start for Bangladesh, it swung away and the back foot drive produced a thick outside edge
fired into the pads, strikes the thigh guard, beaten for pace slightly
outside off, punched away behind square and timed well wide of third man, too much width
forward to a length ball around off stump, played towards point
full length and angled in, whipped out to deep midwicket
forward just outside off, ran off the outside half down to third man
pulled, comes off high on the bat straight to mid on and dropped a very simple chance at head height and Abul Hassan has put it down, very poor indeed
angled in towards off stump, played forward into the covers
dropped into midwicket with the wrists from outside off, good running brings two
angled in too straight and worked out to deep square leg, fine leg is up for that's a dangerous line
short ball outside off, ducked
down the wicket, reached for and slugged into the leg side, this evades deep square
full ball just outside off, played to cover
too much width, Hafeez leans out and drives on the up with superb timing past extra cover
outside off, a lean forward and block towards cover
another drive, this time to point, again pretty well timed from outside off
mistimed straight drive, runs towards mid on, they race through for the single
very good bumper, sharply ducked, it was well directed
just outside off, punched off the back foot to extra cover
fired into the pads, a cry for lbw, not out, it was sliding down
forward to a ball just outside off, ran up towards mid off, they take a quick single
length ball outside off and clubbed over mid off for a one bounce four, slapped away clearing the front leg, super strike but you can't offer them width
short ball drifts down the leg side, out of the reach of the keeper, oh dear
short again, and pulled for four behind square, so comfortable in helping that around the corner
short again and this is taken from outside off all the way for six over wide midwicket, fine strike
full ball around off stump, driven without timing it up towards mid off
timed well enough to chip it over mid off and it runs away for four, the pitch made the shot fly away, wasn't perfectly timed, a little low on the bat
back of a length, goes to pull, gets it high on the pad and it bloobs into the on side short of the deep fielder
fuller just outside off, only a block to cover
length ball on the stumps, a brief step to leg and smashed over extra cover, lovely timing
pulled and it's away for another boundary, bit of a top edge but sails over the rope
length ball around off stump, punched to extra cover
too short, but only cut to cover point
back to cut and missed, this is good stuff, just skidded on a bit
little too wide, cut hard but a fine diving save from Hossain at point saves four
too short this is, slapped to the cover fence, poor ball punished, found the gap well
back cut from just outside off to short third man, they scamper a quick run
slides on with the arm, huge lbw appeal, was it going down? Too high perhaps too
down the wicket and slapped down to long on
down the wicket, lost it in the flight, has to reach out and just block it
a reach outside off and block towards cover point
slung down the leg side, well taken from the keeper
back of a length, pushed out to deep cover hanging back
back again, played to deep midwicket
tossed up outside off, slapped out to deep midwicket
straighter and clipped down to long on on the back foot
great shot, two steps down and lifted up and over extra cover, races to the rope, smart batting and lovely timing
step back and cracked wide of long off again, just two this time as the fielder comes round
full on a length, driven solidly down to long on
step down again, dropped in shorter and played back to the bowler
starts wide of off stump but it bounces a little and flies through to the keeper, nice that
short and pulled between long leg and deep square leg
slower ball outside off, the back cut misses but the keeper fumbles and they steal a bye
back of a length on the stumps, went to back foot drive and got it back to the bowler
short and helped on it's way down the leg side, two between the deep fielders
full and wide, driven at and missed
middle and leg, went to sweep, runs off the pad towards square leg
short and hammered into the stands, another poor ball dragged down and it's lifted over the pickets with superb timing once more
outside off, reached for, comes off a whirl of an outside edge towards deep cover but it lands short of the fielder
back and cut only back to the bowler off a bottom edge
sliding in with the angle, played out to deep cover
forward and blocked around middle and off stumps
pulled into the leg side, mistimed, but the deep backward square can't get in to take it
cut out to deep cover from off stump
too short, rocked back and cut to the cover fence in front of the sweeper, powerfully punished again
around the wicket, full and straighter, dropped into midwicket
delicate late cut but only to short third man
goes to sweep from outside leg stump, runs off the pad to the 45
too short, AGAIN, but the cut stroke can only find extra cover
back of a length and it's flicked away between backward square and midwicket, oh what timing, it's raced between the fielders amazing shot
another shot one and can you guess? put away to cow corner on the pull, awful ball, 14th boundary
full, dabbed to short third man, good running
back of a length again, lucky to only be pulled down to long on
waited for and late cut to short third man
middle and off, driven into the covers for a single
step down and slugged to long on, wasn't quite to the pitch, a sliding fumble allows the second
chopped cut to point, they run, a direct hit to the non-striker's end would have seen a run out
down the wicket, again not to the pitch, slugged through the leg side off an inside edge
middle stump line, coming down, slapped past the bowler, more runs as long off comes round
sliding in, flicked with the angle to short long leg
back of the hand slower ball, goes down on one knee and taken from outside off wide of midwicket for another boundary
length ball around off stump, clearing the front leg and smashing past the bowler, a sliding save from long off

length outside off, a tennis shot down the ground and caught at long off, a really entertaining knock is ended by Nasir's greed of trying to hit another ball to the rope, got it low on the bat and it was straight to the fielder who this time managed to hold on
outside off, back foot push to deep cover
back of a length and flicked through square leg
outside off, a faint edge and caught behind. It was a full wide ball that Hafeez chased, reaching for it got a thin edge to the keeper
played with the turn towards mid on coming forward
waited for and late cut to short third man, they dash through for the single but surely there shouldn't be a run there, it was straight to the fielder
pushed through a tough quicker, tucked past midwicket
stayed in the crease and clipped a middle and leg ball wide enough of short long leg for a single
step down the wicket, dropped in short, waited for and slapped down to long off
tossed up nicely, ran back to the bowler from just outside off
too wide and driven past point, placed well and timed really well, almost reached for it too much stepping to leg
goodness me is this guy in form, step back into the crease and takes a length ball around middle and leg around square leg onto the grass banks, what a shot that it
fuller outside off, driven down to long off
too straight to the right-hander, flicked wide of long leg, four more, well timed
short and outside off, uppercut over backward point into the fact, that is terrible, terrible bowling, awful delivery and slapped to the fence
much better, full and driven to mid off
length ball, flicked past midwicket to the man in the deep
reverse swept from outside leg stump to the cover sweeper
back and pulled hard past mid on, powerful strike
on one knee to slog sweep, comes off the toe of the bat and goes towards long on, who takes the catch! But then falls on the rope, sums it up really
angled in, runs off the front pad to short long leg
wide and full, slapped away past point for four more
back and punched down to long on
back to play to leg, off a leading edge past cover
full towards middle and off, played down to long on
length ball, down to slog sweep, miscued, comes off a bottom edge to the 45
fired in full, dug out to midwicket
nice and full again, dug out past the bowler for a single
good yorker...too little too late...dug out past the bowler
slower ball onto leg stump, clipped down to long leg
full and wide, just inside the guideline so not a wide, Tim Southee-esque that delivery
short and left outside off stump, called wide, obviously bounced too high
length ball outside off and slapped past mid off to finish it in fitting style, clearing the front leg, another lovely strike
